Usage: vcpe service <service> <subcommand> [flags]

Targets a specific service type (bng, mv1, webpa, routerd, xb10, client) with a subcommand (status, logs, up, down, build). For down, --name and --force are required.

Optional flags:
  --name <deployment>     Required for service down: selects the deployment
  --force                 Required for service down: confirms teardown
  --manifest <path>       Required for service up and build
  --state-root <path>     Override the default state root directory
  --json                  Emit structured JSON output

Examples:
  vcpe service bng status
  vcpe service bng logs --name bng-7
  vcpe service bng down --name bng-7 --force
